		"DOTA_Tooltip_ability_item_bloodstone_2"						            "BloodStoneⅡ"
		"DOTA_Tooltip_ability_item_bloodstone_2_Description"						"<h1>Active: Bloodpact</h1>Over %restore_duration% seconds, converts %mana_cost_percentage%%% of max mana into health regeneration, applies a basic dispel, and increases Spell Lifesteal by %lifesteal_multiplier%x.\n<h1>Passive: Mana Spring</h1>Each charge grants %regen_per_charge% mana regeneration per second and %amp_per_charge%%% Spell Amplification. Gain %kill_charges% charges when an enemy hero dies nearby. Bloodstone loses %death_charges% charges when its holder dies. Starts with %initial_charges_tooltip% charges."
		"DOTA_Tooltip_ability_item_bloodstone_2_Lore"								"The Bloodstone's bright ruby color is unmistakable on the battlefield, as the owner seems to have infinite vitality and spirit."
